body:
Actually, overriding `pthread_atfork` via `LD_PRELOAD` does not always work. See [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/46845496/ld-preload-and-linkage) for details.

Yet another solution is to override `fork` via `LD_PRELOAD` with this:
```
pid_t fork(void) {
  return syscall(SYS_clone, SIGCHLD, 0);
}
```

This seems to work now (see my recent referenced commit).
